                <h1>Ultimate Guide to Preparing Walls for Wallpaper</h1>
                <p>Preparing walls for wallpaper is essential for a professional finish. Start by clearing the area and removing any old wallpaper. Clean the walls to eliminate dirt and grease, then patch up holes and imperfections with spackle. Ensure the surface is smooth and primed, promoting better adhesion and a stunning final look.</p>
